<HEADLINE>
FT  26 APR 94 / London Stock Exchange: Chemicals active
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, CHRIS PRICE and PETER JOHN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Chemical stocks outflanked the bears yesterday with the help of a
recommendation from one leading UK securities house which highlighted their
exposure to a pick-up in mainland Europe. Sentiment surrounding the sector
also benefited from a strong set of figures delivered by Du Pont of the US.
The chemicals research team from Smith New Court stood up at the morning
meeting to highlight Courtaulds - which has a 30 per cent exposure to the
continent, and Laporte and ICI - which both have a 25 per cent exposure.
Analyst Mr Philip Morrish said: 'We have been speaking to companies which
are seeing a surprisingly buoyant start to the year particularly in Germany
but also in France and Italy.'
ICI was up 11 at best before closing 3 better at 832p. The shares have risen
sharply over the past week and some dealers said that the company's first
quarter figures on Thursday could prompt a small setback as the company
tends to adopt a cautious stance when it reports. Courtaulds, which reports
in mid May, settled 2 weaker at 545p after 550p earlier and Laporte improved
7 to 797p.
