good first quarter results from Telefonos de Mexico.
Mexican stocks registered their biggest advance in more than three years
last Friday after the Banco de Mexico moved decisively to protect the peso
and quell speculation.
On Friday, the 36-share IPC closed 133.99, or 6.5 per cent higher at
2,209.31, its biggest single-day advance in percentage terms since 17
January 1991.
